09/02/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Agriculture Ministry on Thursday (February 8th) confirmed an outbreak of bird flu in the southeastern province of Batman. The ministry explained that at least 170 chickens had died in a village there and that the ministry is conducting tests to determine if the H5N1 strain is involved. Authorities also announced that four children from the village have been hospitalised as a precaution. The ministry suspects wild birds caused this outbreak. Special teams have been sent to the province to impose quarantines and cull poultry to prevent any further spread. (Zaman - 09/02/07; Anadolu Agency, Cihan, Reuters, AP, BBC - 08/02/07)
